success.question_text: If she continues the pattern, how many cubes will be used in Figure 6?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Patterns

stimulus_1.text: Karan builds a pattern of towers using cubes.

review_3.column_1_text:
The pattern of towers uses cubes in this sequence: 1, 3, 6, 10, …

Each row in each figure uses one more cube than the row above it.

So Figure 5 would need 10 + 5 = 15 cubes, and Figure 6 would need 15 + 6 = 21 cubes.

Karan would need 21 cubes to build Figure 6.

Tip

To find a particular term in a sequence, discover the rule and then write out the terms until you arrive at your answer. If the pattern is simple, you may be able to skip terms.

stimulus_1.text: Karan builds a pattern of towers using cubes.

Tip

success.question_text: What is the smallest number of balls Greg can have?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Number / Division

stimulus_2.text:
Greg has some golf balls and he wants to give them all away.

If he shares the balls equally between three friends, there is one left over.

If he shares the balls equally between four friends, there is one left over.

If he shares the balls equally between five friends, there is one left over.

review_3.column_1_text:
If Greg had one less golf ball to give away then there would be an equal number when shared between 3, 4 or 5 people. So the number of golf balls must be one more than a multiple of 3, 4 and 5.

The smallest number that both 4 and 5 divide into is 4 × 5 = 20.

The smallest number that both 3 and 20 divide into is 3 × 20 = 60.

So the smallest multiple of 3, 4 and 5 is 60.

Add one for the leftover ball.

This means that Greg has 61 golf balls.

review_4.column_1_text:
Tip

A common multiple of two numbers can be found by multiplying the numbers. If two numbers have no factors in common (apart from 1), then their product will be the lowest common multiple.

The scale is 1 unit = 4 km, so 6 units = 24 km.

Abcliffe to Lonsdale is about 24 km.

Tip

When a map is drawn on a grid, a scale is used to represent distance. Take care to express answers with correct units, whether it is metres, kilometres, etc.

success.question_text: If Dimity is 16, how old is Pierce?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Number / Problem Solving

stimulus_1.text:
Brian is 24 years younger than Pierce.

Dave is one-fifth the age of Brian.

Dimity is 12 years older than Dave.

review_3.column_1_text:
Commence with 16-year-old Dimity.

As Dimity is 16, then Dave is 16 – 12 = 4 years old.

As Dave is one-fifth the age of Brian, then Brian is 5 × 4 = 20 years old.

As Brian is 24 years younger than Pierce, then Pierce is 24 + 20 = 44 years old.

Pierce is 44 years old.

Tip

Addition and subtraction are inverse (or opposite) operations. Multiplication and division are also inverse (or opposite) operations.

30 km – 20 km = 10 km.

review_7.column_1_text:

Tip
